snippet.textDisplay: Duck is so Christmas-y!!  In Denmark, Christmas dinner just about always consists of either a pork roast or a whole roast duck, or both... :D Add to that, boiled potatoes, brown potatoes (Made by frying them off in caramel) and crisps, braised red cabbage with orange and almonds, pickled cucumbers, redcurrant jelly and two different kinds of gravy, one for each kind of meat...  And for dessert, Ris'ala'mande, which is a rice pudding that is basically 50% whipped cream...  And then we all roll each other home, if we're not able to emulate a bouncy ball instead... XD
snippet.textOriginal: Duck is so Christmas-y!!  In Denmark, Christmas dinner just about always consists of either a pork roast or a whole roast duck, or both... :D Add to that, boiled potatoes, brown potatoes (Made by frying them off in caramel) and crisps, braised red cabbage with orange and almonds, pickled cucumbers, redcurrant jelly and two different kinds of gravy, one for each kind of meat...  And for dessert, Ris'ala'mande, which is a rice pudding that is basically 50% whipped cream...  And then we all roll each other home, if we're not able to emulate a bouncy ball instead... XD
